---
description: Definition of done for generated changes
globs: ["**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

A task is not done unless the change is production-credible.

Definition of done:
- implementation is complete for the requested scope
- no placeholder branches remain
- types are coherent
- error paths are handled
- architecture boundaries are respected
- code fits repository conventions
- obvious edge cases are considered
- affected tests are added or updated where appropriate
- no unrelated churn is included

Do not mark a task complete when:
- only happy path exists
- implementation is mostly scaffold
- architecture shortcuts were taken without explanation
- the code compiles conceptually but misses flow-critical behavior